nouns.description: catfish (countable and uncountable, plural catfish or catfishes)

entries.meaning: Any fish of the order Siluriformes, mainly found in fresh water, lacking scales, and having barbels like whiskers around the mouth.
examples: Synonyms: (Africa) catlet, sheat, sheatfish, river chicken

entries.meaning: The meat of such a fish, popular in the Southern U.S. and Central Europe.

verbs.description: catfish (third-person singular simple present catfishes, present participle catfishing, simple past and past participle catfished)

examples: I only use this rod for catfishing.

description: From the 2010 documentary Catfish, supposedly inspired by the practice of fishermen keeping cod active by storing them with catfish (see sense 1) which nip at their tails.

entries.meaning: (Internet) Someone who creates a fake profile on a social media platform in order to deceive people.

verbs.description: catfish (third-person singular simple present catfishes, present participle catfishing, simple past and past participle catfished)

entries.meaning: (Internet, slang, transitive) To create and operate a fake online profile to deceive (someone).
